webpackJsonp([0xf1b82f24ec5d],{5707:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{post:{html:"<p>Sometimes spam can be funny. A few weeks ago, I got a Klez-infected spam  forged from  'der  at shockwellenreiter.de'. I thought that was funny so I told <a href=\"http://www.schockwellenreiter.de/\">Der Schockwellenreiter</a> about it.</p>\n<p>Yesterday, my Spam Bouncer caught a Klez-infected bounced mail. Someone had forged <em>my</em> address in a spam to 'der  at shockwellenreiter.de', and Jörg either manually or automatically bounced it ('X-Mailer: Apple Mail (2.482)'), but it bounced to me and not to the Klez-infected spammer (in Russia? 'Received: from mx5.mail.ru (mx5.mail.ru [194.67.57.15])...). </p>\n<p>So now I guess it's Jörg's turn again to spam me.</p>",fields:{title:"Spam Ping Pong With Der Schockwellenreiter",date:"01 Sep 2002",url:"https://papascott.de/2002-09-01-spam-ping-pong-with-der-schockwellenreiter/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2002-09-01-spam-ping-pong-with-der-schockwellenreiter/",prev:{fields:{title:"Jaguar",date:"30 Aug 2002",slug:"/2002-08-30-jaguar/"}},next:{fields:{title:"Welcome Home,  and What's Your Name Now?",date:"01 Sep 2002",slug:"/2002-09-01-welcome-home-and-whats-your-name-now/"}}}}}});
